data.title: Google My Business Categories (Complete List – 2024)
data.meta_description: This Google My Business categories list includes over 4,000 categories, and how to choose business categories to rank in search and maps.
data.text:
There are 100s of Google My Business (now called Google Business Profile) categories to choose from, and a lot of them can seem a bit vague. In fact, there are over 4,000 categories, and Google doesn’t exactly provide any help on choosing what is best.

Follow this guide to optimize business categories on your profile:

What Are Google My Business Categories?

How To Choose The Best Google My Business Categories

How To Find Competitor Business Categories

The Complete List of Google My Business Categories

What Are Google My Business Categories?

Google My Business categories help your profile show for relevant searches in Google Maps and Local 3-Pack and help potential customers find local businesses when performing localized searches. When creating a Google My Business Listing, one of the first steps is to choose a business category. This consists of setting 1 primary category and up to 9 additional business categories.

This is one of the biggest ranking factors in Local Pack.

In fact, optimizing Google My Business categories can make a HUGE impact…

As of February 17th, 2024, there are 4102 Google My Business categories, which are frequently updated by Google. In the last 30 days, 11 new Google Business Profile categories were added: Animal cafe, Eastern European grocery store, European grocery store, Palestinian restaurant, Applied behavior analysis therapist, EMDR Psychotherapist, Gestalt Therapist, Go club, Gutter service, Home staging service, and Lactation service.

Pro Tip: You can use this guide to find competitor categories including their primary category and any additional secondary categories that they are using.

Here’s how to choose the best categories for your business…

How To Choose The Best Business Categories

The best way to select categories for Google My Business (GMB) is to align them with business goals.

Choose the best business categories by determining the following:

Profitability – Select categories that align with the most profitable services.

Volume – Choose categories with high search volume keywords.

Competitors – Compare categories with local competitors.

Usually, less is more and your selection should follow Google’s Guidelines to avoid a suspension due to quality issues.

Note: It’s possible to change primary and secondary business categories at any time. Use this guide to change the primary category and any additional categories on your profile.

How To Find Competitor Business Categories

Another good strategy for choosing business categories is to research the competition.

Here’s how to find competitor business categories:

Install the Phantom Google Chrome Extension

Perform a search for your target keyword or competitor in Google Search or Maps

The extension will automatically display all categories for any Business Profile (see below)

You can see the full guide on how to find competitor Google My Business categories for more information about the extension and finding categories manually.

Pro Tip: Include these category optimizations in LocalBusiness Schema Markup, Local Citations, and other local listings to further increase relevance signals.

The Complete List of Google My Business Categories

This Google My Business category list is sorted alphabetically. If you have trouble finding a category that best describes your business, try using a broader category.
